\newlabel{fig:es_state}{{10}{21}{State-level event-study estimates: effect of AI Geographic Exposure (AIGE) on $\log (\text {Business Applications})$ relative to November 2022 ($t = 0$). Shaded band is the 95\,\% confidence interval based on state-clustered standard errors (56 clusters). State and month fixed effects included. Coefficients are statistically insignificant throughout}{figure.caption.21}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11}{\ignorespaces State-level event-study estimates for four BFS series. Each panel plots the interaction coefficient between AI Geographic Exposure (AIGE) and a month-relative-to-November-2022 indicator, estimated on the state $\times $ month panel. BA = total applications; HBA = high-propensity applications; WBA = applications with planned wages; CBA = corrected applications. Business formation series (BF4Q, BF8Q, etc.) are not published at state level by the Census Bureau. Shaded bands are 95\,\% confidence intervals based on state-clustered standard errors (56 clusters). All specifications include state and month fixed effects. Dashed vertical line marks November~2022 ($t = 0$).}}{22}{figure.caption.22}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:es_state_facet}{{11}{22}{State-level event-study estimates for four BFS series. Each panel plots the interaction coefficient between AI Geographic Exposure (AIGE) and a month-relative-to-November-2022 indicator, estimated on the state $\times $ month panel. BA = total applications; HBA = high-propensity applications; WBA = applications with planned wages; CBA = corrected applications. Business formation series (BF4Q, BF8Q, etc.) are not published at state level by the Census Bureau. Shaded bands are 95\,\% confidence intervals based on state-clustered standard errors (56 clusters). All specifications include state and month fixed effects. Dashed vertical line marks November~2022 ($t = 0$)}{figure.caption.22}{}}
